narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: For the first time, I analyzed the causes and effects of a range of emotions. This content was frequently made relevant and applicable to real, and particularly political, life.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Overall pretty solid course. One suggestion would be a little less time on establishing the various philosophical frameworks at the beginning and more on applications to concrete political situations.

The course's strengths are: interesting subject material, knowledeable professor, Weaknesses are primarily structural: I never really felt like there was anything that tied the course material or concepts together in a powerful way; each week is almost indepedent of the others in terms of content.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Pretty good course. Wouldn't say it is a must-take class but its generally pretty interesting. Definitely will get more out of it the more reading you do, but that's always true.

YES YES YES, Professor Oskian is amazing, I feel like she's a sage who knows just about everything. The discussion about emotions is always rich. I hate philosophy, but this political philosophy class was so good.
Yes, I would definitely recommend this course!!
